article.headline: Texas-Arlington 66, Stephen F.Austin 65
article.story: ARLINGTON, Texas -- Bo Ingram tied the game in overtime, then scored the winning basket in UTSA's 66-65 victory over Stephen F. Austin on Wednesday night. Ingram, whose 15 points led the Mavericks (12-12, 6-5 Southland), watched his team fall behind 64-61 with 1:50 left in overtime. But he converted a three-point play, then hit a jumper with 55 seconds left for a 66-64 edge. Dion Prewster made one free throw to cut it to 66-65, but the Lumberjacks (15-8, 6-5) missed two short shots in the final seconds. Shaquille White-Miller added 10 points, including a 3-pointer followed by one from Bryant Smith with 17 seconds left that forced overtime. Jereal Scott's 19 points led the Lumberjacks, whose three-game winning streak ended. Eddie Williams had a double-double of 13 points and 12 rebounds. Stephen F. Austin led 45-30 midway through the second half before the Mavericks' late push.
